nal Post| date=December 27, 2017}}</ref> The first manned mission to Mars was launched in 2015 and returned to Earth in 2018.\n|-\n| ''[[A Scanner Darkly]]''\n| Novel\n| 1977\n| 1994\n|A narcotics agent wears a \"scramble suit\" that hides his identity and uses video to spy on a drug-using household. [[A Scanner Darkly (film)|Made into a film]] in 2006.\n|-\n| ''[[Sci-Fighters]]''\n| Film\n| 1996\n| 2009\n| A convict escapes from the Moon and returns to Earth on the run, carrying a deadly virus.<ref name=\"movie pilot\"/>\n|-\n| ''[[Sekirei]]''\n| Manga, Anime\n| 2004\n| 2020\n| Takes place in Tokyo of the \"New Eastern Imperial Capital\", where \"Sekirei\" (women fighters) battle to determine the fate of the world.\n|-\n| ''[[The Secret People]]''\n| Novel\n| 1935\n| 1964\n|[[Elizabeth II|Queen Elizabeth II]] is named as the reigning monarch of the United Kingdom; however, when the novel was published in 1935, she was only third in the line of succession.\n|-\n| ''[[Senran Kagura]]''\n| Video game\n| 2011\n| 2020\n| Female ninjas are commonplace and fight off evil.\n|-\n| ''[[The Sentinel (short story)|The Sentinel]]'' \n| Short story\n| 1951\n| 1996\n| An expedition to [[Mare Crisium]] unearths an alien artifact. The inspiration for ''[[2001: A Space Odyssey]]''. \n|-\n| ''[[The Sentinels of the New Dawn]]'' (from ''[[Doctor Who]]'')\n| Audio drama\n| 2011\n| 2014\n| This audio drama correctly predicted that there would be a [[West African Ebola virus epidemic|widespread Ebola epidemic]] in 2014.\n|-\n|''[[Seven Days in May]]''\n|Film\n|1964\n|1970\n|A plot by the Soviet Union to take over the United States is discovered by military leaders.\n|-\n| ''[[Sexmission]]''\n| Film\n| 1984\n| 1991\n|By 1991, [[suspended animation]] has been perfected. Begins in 1991, when the main characters enter hibernation, before awakening in 2044.\n|-\n| ''[[The Shadows of Avalon]]'' (from ''[[Doctor Who]]'')\n| Novel\n| 2000\n| 2012\n| By 2012, the United Kingdom has a king.\n|-\n|