ion food gives cyclists the strength and stamina to keep up with the train. Love machines can make one person fall in love with another.\n|-\n| ''[[Superman (comic book)|Superman]]'' #128\n| Comic\n| 1959\n| 2000\n| By 2000, Earth has a [[world government]] led by the President of the United Worlds, Mars has been colonized and space travel is common. All of the planet's oceans were dissolved due to an atomic experiment.\n|-\n| ''[[Superman (comic book)|Superman]]'' #300\n| Comic\n| 1976\n| 1990\u20132001\n| By 1990, the [[Empire State Building|New Empire State Building]] has regained its status as the [[List of tallest buildings|tallest building in the world]], an impenetrable dome has been built around the [[White House]] to protect the US President and a [[Colonization of the Moon|moonbase]] has been built by the United States, equipped with a [[Space weapon|destructive laser beam weapon]]. In that year, [[World War III]] was averted by [[Superman|Skyboy]], who came to Earth in 1976. 3D television known as Tri-Vision was invented prior to 2001. On January 1, 2001, [[Boston]], [[New York City]], [[Philadelphia]] and [[Washington, DC]] merged to form the huge city of [[Metropolis (comics)|Metropolis]].\n|-\n| ''[[Superman (comic book)|Superman]]'' #400\n| Comic\n| 1984\n| 1990s\n| In the 1990s, World War III was averted by the efforts of Kuhan Pei-Jing.\n|-\n| ''[[Supervolcano (film)|Supervolcano]]''\n| Docudrama film\n| 2005\n| 2020\n| The caldera of [[Yellowstone National Park]] undergoes a [[supereruption]].<ref name=Volcano>{{cite web|title=TV programs worth watching|url=http://www.cpa.org.au/garchve05/1223worth.html|publisher=Cpa.org.au|accessdate=2015-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081204174756/http://www.cpa.org.au/garchve05/1223worth.html|archive-date=2008-12-04|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Surrogates]]''\n|Film\n|2009\n|2017\n|Humans live at home and interact with the world through remotely operated androids. \n|-\n|''[[SWAT 3]]''\n|Vi