09. Reanimated corpses are placed in cybernetic exoskeletons. The President of the United States is a clone who resigns and forms a paramilitary group.<ref name=\"wc9\"/><ref name=\"wc10\"/><ref name=\"gamesradar\">{{cite web|url=https://gamesradar.com/8-games-that-did-a-terrible-job-predicting-the-future/|title=8 games that did a terrible job predicting the future|author=|date=|work=gamesradar.com|accessdate=April 15, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Metal Gear Solid 4: Guns of the Patriots]]''\n| Video game\n| 2008\n| 2014\n| Set nine years after the events of the original ''Metal Gear Solid''<ref name=\"QUOTEnineyears\">{{cite video game|title=Metal Gear Solid 4: Guns of the Patriots |developer=[[Kojima Productions]] |publisher=[[Konami]] |date=June 12, 2008 |platform=[[PlayStation 3]]|quote='''Naomi''': I haven't seen you since Shadow Moses. How long? Ten years? / '''Snake''': Nine. }}</ref> and five years after ''Sons of Liberty''.<ref name=\"QUOTEfiveyears\">{{cite video game|title=Metal Gear Solid 4: Guns of the Patriots |developer=[[Kojima Productions]] |publisher=[[Konami]]\n|date=June 12, 2008 |platform=[[PlayStation 3]]|quote='''Snake''': GW? The same GW we destroyed five years ago? }}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[M\u00e9xico 2000]]''\n| Film\n| 1983\n| 2000\n| By 2000, [[Mexico]] is a [[utopia]]n society.\n|-\n| \"[[Miami 2017 (Seen the Lights Go Out on Broadway)]]\"\n|Song\n|1976\n|2017\n|In the story of this post-apocalyptic song by [[Billy Joel]], a man moves to [[Miami]] after [[New York City|New York]] is devastated by a disaster in 2017. \n|-\n| \"Millennium\" (from ''[[My Life and Times]]'')\n| TV series episode\n| 1991\n| 1999\u20132000\n| In 1999, there are numerous doomsday conspiracy theories that [[List of dates predicted for apocalyptic events|the world will end in 2000]].\n|-\n| \"[[Millennium (The X-Files)|Millennium]]\" (from ''[[The X-Files]]'')\n|TV series episode\n| 1999\n| 1999\u20132000\n| Depicts New Year's Eve 1999 and New Year's Day 2000. References t